 :tx/rationale "DESIGN: Completion-Bound Verification (CBV) — the missing guard at the completion boundary. Just as SFE guards task creation and WITNESS guards spec verification, CBV guards task completion. Three modes: --verify (automated from acceptance criteria), --attest (agent provides evidence string), --force (bypass with recorded skip). Default: parse 'ACCEPTANCE:' text from task description, attempt automated verification. If verification fails, block closure. Self-improving: retrospective tracks premature closure rate by completion mode. DUAL of witness system: witnesses verify spec elements, CBV verifies task completion. Both require proof for state transitions. ALGEBRAIC: done morphism becomes a witnessed morphism carrying evidence. INV-TASK-006: braid done extracts acceptance criteria and requires confirmation or evidence before Closed transition. TRACES TO: C5 (Traceability), INV-WITNESS-001 (evidence-backed transitions), FM-035 (ideation-to-task skip applied to completion)."
